"Prokushkin A.S., Tokareva I.V., Prokushkin S.G., Abaimov A.P., Guggenberger H.","Fluxes of dissolved organic matter in larch forests in the cryolithozone of central Siberia",2008,"Russian Journal of Ecology","39","3",,"151","159",,,10.1134/S1067413608030016,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-43549104919&partnerID=40&md5=ce4153ecaf316f08a7fe62ce238facee","Sukachev Institute of Forest, Siberian Branch, Russian Academy of Sciences, Akademgorodok, Krasnoyarsk, 660036, Russian Federation; Martin Luther University, Halle (Saale), D-06108, Germany","Prokushkin, A.S., Sukachev Institute of Forest, Siberian Branch, Russian Academy of Sciences, Akademgorodok, Krasnoyarsk, 660036, Russian Federation; Tokareva, I.V., Sukachev Institute of Forest, Siberian Branch, Russian Academy of Sciences, Akademgorodok, Krasnoyarsk, 660036, Russian Federation; Prokushkin, S.G., Sukachev Institute of Forest, Siberian Branch, Russian Academy of Sciences, Akademgorodok, Krasnoyarsk, 660036, Russian Federation; Abaimov, A.P., Sukachev Institute of Forest, Siberian Branch, Russian Academy of Sciences, Akademgorodok, Krasnoyarsk, 660036, Russian Federation; Guggenberger, H., Martin Luther University, Halle (Saale), D-06108, Germany","Fluxes of dissolved organic matter (DOM) in larch biogeocenoses and its export from the drainage basin have been studied in the zone of continuous permafrost. A comparative assessment of DOM input into the soil has been made on slopes of northern and southern exposures (as variants reflecting the current state and warming). The dynamics of DOM export in a creek depending on the increasing depth of the active soil horizon in the drainage area have been revealed. It is concluded that an increase in the depth of the seasonally thawing layer induced by global warming will not have any significant effect on the amount of annual DOM export. Reduction of DOM export may be expected upon a decrease in litter stocks under the effect of their mineralization and forest fires. © 2008 MAIK Nauka.","Creek; Dissolved organic matter; Drainage basin; Export; Larch biogeocenoses; Permafrost","assessment method; comparative study; coniferous forest; dissolved organic matter; drainage basin; forest fire; permafrost; Eurasia; Siberia; Larix",,,,,,"Anisimov, O.A., Belolutskaya, M.A., Modeling the Impact of Anthropogenic Warming on Permafrost: Taking into Account the Influence of Vegetation (2004) Meteorol. Gidrol., (11), pp. 73-81; Christ, M.J., David, M.B., Temperature and Moisture Effects on the Production of Dissolved Organic Carbon in Spodosol (1996) Soil Biol. Biochem., (28), pp. 1191-1199; Freeman, C., Evans, C.D., Monteith, D.T., Export of Organic Carbon from Peat Soils (2001) Nature, 412, p. 785. , 6849; Gorbacheva, T.T., Lukina, N.V., Organic Carbon in Podzolic Soil Waters in Green Moss Spruce Forests of the Kola Peninsula (2004) Lesovedenie, (4), pp. 43-50; Guggenberger, G., Kaiser, K., Dissolved Organic Matter in Soil: Challenging the Paradigm of Sorptive Preservation (2003) Geoderma, 113, pp. 293-310; Hansell, D.A., Kadko, D., Bates, N.R., Degradation of Terrigenous Dissolved Organic Carbon in the Western Arctic Ocean (2004) Science, 304, pp. 858-861. , 5672; Hobbie, S.E., Schimel, J.P., Trumbore, S.E., Control over Carbon Storage and Turnover in High-Latitude Soils (2000) Glob. Change Biol., (6), pp. 196-210; Hongve, D., Van Hees, P.A.W., Lunsdrom, D., Dissolved Components in Precipitation Water Percolated through Forest Litter (2000) Eur. J. Soil Sci., 51, pp. 667-677; Izrael, Yu.A., Pavlov, A.V., Anokhin, Yu.A., Cryolithozone Evolution under Conditions of Recent Global Climate Change (2002) Meteorol. Gidrol., (1), pp. 22-34; Jarvis, P., Saugier, B., Schulze, E.-D., Roy, J., Saugier, B., Mooney, H.A., Productivity of Boreal Forests (2001) Terrestrial Global Productivity, pp. 189-244. , Academic San Diego; Kaiser, K., Guggenberger, G., Haumaier, L., Seasonal Variations in the Chemical Composition of Dissolved Organic Mat